notesStmt.note: A damaged leaf containing text and marginal notes from an unrelated manuscript is laid in.
Item cataloged from digitized facsimile and existing description.

msIdentifier.repository: Library at the Herbert D. Katz Center for Advanced Judaic Studies

msContents.summary: Copy of a work on grammar; neatly written. A few pages at the beginning and end have had the edges restored, obscuring some text.

author.persName: Ibn Hishām, ʻAbd Allāh ibn Yūsuf, 1309-1360
ابن هشام، عبد الله بن يوسف

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh script; pointed, partially vocalized.

binding.p: Brown leather over pasteboard (Type III); rebacked with red spine and edges; blind stamped central mandorla with two pendants on the vertical axis.

origin.p: The item is undated; perhaps copied in the 16th century.

history.provenance: Gift of Mayer Sulzberger to the library of the Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning (bookplate inside front cover), possibly in 1912 (pencil note, first flyleaf recto).
